<h1>Leo Babauta</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://zenhabits.net/now/">zenhabits.net/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Davis
CA
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Creator of Zen Habits (<a href="http://zenhabits.net)">http://zenhabits.net)</a>
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I help people change their lives through habits, mindfulness and simplicity.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I try to help people because I remember what it was like to be stuck, unhealthy, deeply in debt, stressed out, and unhappy.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
Changing habits isn't about creating a set routine ... it's a way of learning about ourselves. Sticking with something isn't about having a set way in life, but about staying with uncertainty, discomfort, groundlessness.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
Don Quixote, by Cervantes
</p>

